SECTION 4 — SERVER INSTALLATION (run on the server as Administrator)
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

── 4.1 Install in this exact order ──────────────────────────────────────────────

    1. python-3.11.x-amd64.exe        (if Python not already installed)
       - Check "Add Python to PATH" during install

    2. rewrite_amd64_en-US.msi        (URL Rewrite)

    3. ARRv3_setup_amd64_en-US.exe    (Application Request Routing)


── 4.2 Enable ARR Proxy Mode ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

In IIS Manager:
    Server node (top level, not a site)
    → Application Request Routing Cache
    → Server Proxy Settings (right pane)
    → Check "Enable proxy"
    → Apply


── 4.3 Copy Files to Server ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    C:\sas-relay\
        backend\          (Python app)
        backend\.env      (production env)
        backend\saml\     (SAML certs)
        dist\             (frontend build — rename from frontend/dist)
        start_backend.bat


── 4.4 Install Python Dependencies ─────────────────────────────────────────────

Open Command Prompt as Administrator:

    cd C:\sas-relay\backend
    pip install -r requirements.txt


── 4.5 Run Database Migrations ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

    cd C:\sas-relay\backend
    alembic upgrade head

Run this once. Confirms DB connection is working.
If it fails, check DATABASE_URL in .env first.


════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
SECTION 5 — START BACKEND VIA TASK SCHEDULER
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Run in Command Prompt as Administrator:

── 5.1 Create the task ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    schtasks /create /tn "SAS Relay Backend" /tr "C:\sas-relay\start_backend.bat" /sc onstart /ru SYSTEM /rl HIGHEST /f

── 5.2 Start it now (no reboot needed) ──────────────────────────────────────────

    schtasks /run /tn "SAS Relay Backend"

── 5.3 Verify port 8000 is listening ────────────────────────────────────────────

    netstat -ano | findstr :8000

Expected output:
    TCP    127.0.0.1:8000    0.0.0.0:0    LISTENING    <PID>

── 5.4 Verify API is responding ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

    curl http://127.0.0.1:8000/auth/me

Expected: 401 Unauthorized (means FastAPI is running, auth is working)

── 5.5 Stop / Restart commands ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

    schtasks /end /tn "SAS Relay Backend"       (stop)
    schtasks /run /tn "SAS Relay Backend"       (start)
    schtasks /delete /tn "SAS Relay Backend" /f (remove task entirely)


