SECTION 8 — THINGS TO HAND OFF TO OTHER TEAMS
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

── Auth / IDP Team ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Give them:
  - ACS URL:       https://<YOUR_DOMAIN>/auth/saml/callback
  - Entity ID:     https://<YOUR_DOMAIN>
  - sp_cert.pem    (public cert only, NOT the private key)

They need to:
  - Register your SP in the IDP
  - Configure attributes to release: displayName, memberOf
  - Confirm IDP metadata URL matches SAML_IDP_METADATA_URL in .env

── AD / LDAP Team ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Confirm:
  - Service account <SERVICE_ACCOUNT> exists with read access to group objects
  - AD groups for admin and helpdesk roles exist and are mapped in the app
  - LDAP_BIND_DN and LDAP_BASE_DN match your AD structure

── DBA Team ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Confirm:
  - PostgreSQL user sas_relay_user exists
  - User has CREATE, SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE on sas_relay database
  - Server firewall allows connection from the app server on port 5432


